Interface ComonadStore<S,A,W extends com.jnape.palatable.lambda.comonad.Comonad<?,W>>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of the storage and the cursor
    A - the type of the value produced
    All Superinterfaces:

    public interface ComonadStore<S,A,W extends com.jnape.palatable.lambda.comonad.Comonad<?,W>>
extends com.jnape.palatable.lambda.comonad.Comonad<A,W>
    An interface for an Store Comonad, which can be thought of as providing a lookup function and a current input. A concrete class is provided in Store.

        ComonadStore<S,A,W> seeks(com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functions.Fn1<? super S,? extends S> f)
        Produce a new store by providing a relative change to the cursor. This can be implemented using the Comonad implementation as: return downcast(this.extend((Fn1<WA, A>) s -> s.peeks(f))); but is left unimplemented in the interface to prevent conflicts from using `seeks` to implement Comonad.extendImpl(com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functions.Fn1<? super com.jnape.palatable.lambda.comonad.Comonad<A, W>, ? extends B>).
        Parameters:
